# 2026-04-19 21:10:18.401245
+Implement the `nmon` package's `__init__.py` file. This is a standard Python package-marker file that makes the containing directory importable as a package and optionally re-exports selected symbols from sibling modules to shorten import paths.
+
+The `__init__.py` file in `src/nmon/` should:
+1. Be a standard Python package marker with no logic
+2. Optionally re-export selected symbols from sibling modules to shorten import paths
+3. Not contain any intra-project imports beyond re-exports
+4. Not own any classes, functions, or module-level constants
+
+NOTE: Do NOT attempt to re-export `TempView` or `LlmView` as classes — they do not exist as classes in their respective modules. `temp_view.py` defines only the functions `render_temp_view` and `update_temp_prefs`; `llm_view.py` defines only `render_llm_view`. If re-exporting these modules, use the correct function names or omit them entirely.
+
+The file may be empty (a standard package marker with no imports), or it may include re-exports like:
+- `Settings` from `nmon.config`
+- `UserPrefs` from `nmon.config`
+- `GpuSnapshot` from `nmon.gpu_monitor`
+- `OllamaSnapshot` from `nmon.ollama_monitor`
+- `AlertState` from `nmon.alerts`
+- `HistoryStore` from `nmon.history`
+- `DashboardView` from `nmon.views.dashboard_view`
+- `render_temp_view`, `update_temp_prefs` from `nmon.views.temp_view` (NOT `TempView`)
+- `PowerView` from `nmon.views.power_view`
+- `render_llm_view` from `nmon.views.llm_view` (NOT `LlmView`)
+- `Sparkline` from `nmon.widgets.sparkline`
+- `AlertBar` from `nmon.widgets.alert_bar`
+
+The exact set is implementation-dependent and may be empty initially.
+
+---
+
