# 2026-04-19 21:11:48.536766
+Implement `GpuSnapshot` dataclass and `GpuMonitorProtocol` in src/nmon/gpu_monitor.py. The module must define:
+
+1. `GpuSnapshot` dataclass with fields:
+   - `gpu_index: int`
+   - `timestamp: float`
+   - `temperature_c: float`
+   - `mem_junction_temp_c: float | None`
+   - `memory_used_mb: float`
+   - `memory_total_mb: float`
+   - `power_draw_w: float`
+   - `power_limit_w: float`
+
+2. `GpuMonitorProtocol` protocol with method:
+   - `poll(self) -> list[GpuSnapshot]`
+
+3. `poll()` function that:
+   - Initializes pynvml if not already initialized
+   - Gets number of GPUs in the system
+   - For each GPU index from 0 to num_gpus - 1:
+     a. Attempt to get the GPU handle
+     b. If handle retrieval fails, log warning and continue to next GPU
+     c. Collect temperature using nvmlDeviceGetTemperature
+     d. Try to collect memory junction temperature using nvmlDeviceGetMemoryBusTemperature; if unavailable, set to None
+     e. Get memory info using nvmlDeviceGetMemoryInfo
+     f. Get power usage using nvmlDeviceGetPowerUsage
+     g. Get power limit using nvmlDeviceGetPowerLimit
+     h. Create a GpuSnapshot with collected data
+   - Return list of GpuSnapshot objects
+
+Error handling:
+- If pynvml init fails, return empty list and log error
+- If GPU handle retrieval fails, skip that GPU and log warning
+- If memory junction temp is not supported, return None for that field
+- All pynvml calls must be wrapped in try/except blocks to prevent crashes
+- Use `import pynvml` and `pynvml.nvmlInit()` to initialize
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(gpu_index)` to get handle
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetTemperature(handle, pynvml.NVML_TEMPERATURE_GPU)` for temp
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetMemoryBusTemperature(handle)` for mem junction temp (may raise exception)
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetMemoryInfo(handle)` for memory info
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetPowerUsage(handle)` for power usage
+- Use `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetPowerLimit(handle)` for power limit
+- Log warnings using `logging.warning()` with descriptive messages
+- Return empty list on pynvml init failure
+
