+Implement OllamaMonitor in src/nmon/ollama_monitor.py. The file must define the OllamaSnapshot dataclass, OllamaMonitorProtocol interface, and OllamaMonitor class with the following specifications:
+
+1. Import Settings from nmon.config and httpx
+2. Define OllamaSnapshot dataclass with:
+   - timestamp: float
+   - reachable: bool
+   - loaded_model: str | None
+   - model_size_bytes: int | None
+   - gpu_use_pct: float | None
+   - cpu_use_pct: float | None
+   - gpu_layers: int | None
+   - total_layers: int | None
+
+3. Define OllamaMonitorProtocol interface with:
+   - async def poll(self, client: httpx.AsyncClient) -> OllamaSnapshot
+
+4. Define OllamaMonitor class with:
+   - __init__(self, settings: Settings) -> None
+   - probe_ollama(client: httpx.AsyncClient, base_url: str) -> bool
+   - async poll(self, client: httpx.AsyncClient) -> OllamaSnapshot
+
+The class should:
+- Initialize with settings and store ollama_detected = False
+- Set ollama_client = None initially
+- Implement probe_ollama that attempts GET /api/tags with 3s timeout
+- If successful, set ollama_detected = True; if any exception, return False
+- Implement poll that:
+  - If not ollama_detected, return OllamaSnapshot(reachable=False, ...)
+  - Attempt GET /api/ps with 3s timeout
+  - If timeout or connection error, return OllamaSnapshot(reachable=False, ...)
+  - Parse response JSON for model info
+  - Extract loaded_model, model_size_bytes, gpu_layers, total_layers
+  - Compute gpu_use_pct = (gpu_layers / total_layers) * 100 if both non-None
+  - Compute cpu_use_pct = 100 - gpu_use_pct if gpu_use_pct is not None
+  - Return OllamaSnapshot with all fields populated
+
