+Write tests for main() function in src/nmon/main.py into tests/test_main.py. The tests must verify that main() correctly loads settings, initializes all subsystems, starts the NmonApp event loop, handles SIGTERM gracefully, persists user preferences on exit, and raises SystemExit when pynvml init fails.
+
+Import the module under test from its production location: from nmon.main import main
+Import required types: from nmon.app import NmonApp
+Import required protocols: from nmon.gpu_monitor import GpuMonitorProtocol
+Import required protocols: from nmon.ollama_monitor import OllamaMonitorProtocol
+Import required dataclasses: from nmon.config import Settings, UserPrefs
+Import required dataclasses: from nmon.history import HistoryStore
+
+Test behaviors:
+- main() loads settings from environment and validates them
+- main() initializes all subsystems (monitors, history store, app)
+- main() starts the NmonApp event loop successfully
+- main() handles SIGTERM gracefully by shutting down all components
+- main() persists user preferences to disk on exit
+- main() raises SystemExit when pynvml init fails
+
+Use pytest fixtures and plugins:
+- pytest-asyncio
+- monkeypatch
+- tmp_path
+
+Mock external dependencies:
+- pynvml (via pytest-mock)
+- httpx.AsyncClient
+- sqlite3.Connection
+- rich.live.Live
+
+Coverage goal: must exercise both happy path and error path (pynvml init failure)
+
+The main() function under test is defined in src/nmon/main.py and has the following signature:
+def main() -> None:
+    1. Load settings from environment using Settings.model_validate_env().
+    2. Initialize HistoryStore with `settings` (pass the Settings object).
+    3. Initialize GpuMonitorProtocol with settings.poll_interval_s.
+    4. Initialize OllamaMonitorProtocol with settings.ollama_base_url, settings.poll_interval_s.
+    5. Load user preferences from prefs_path using UserPrefs.model_validate_json().
+    6. Create NmonApp instance with:
+       - gpu_monitor: GpuMonitorProtocol
+       - ollama_monitor: OllamaMonitorProtocol
+       - history_store: HistoryStore
+       - settings: Settings
+       - prefs: UserPrefs
+    7. Run NmonApp's event loop via app.run().
+    8. On Ctrl+C or SIGTERM, gracefully shut down all monitors and flush history to DB.
+
+The test file must be runnable with `pytest` out of the box; real side effects (disk writes, network calls, GPU access) must be mocked.
+
